    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-23T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-23T07:00:00-05:00" n="887"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d887">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense(M)Turkey/927: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-23T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >February 23, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>319. Department’s 135 February 21, 6 p.m. As reported in my 284 February 18, 1
                    p.m., I have already made a vigorous protest in writing. In subsequent
                    conversation with the Secretary General of the Foreign Office,<note n="12"
                        xml:id="d887fn12">Cevat Acikalin.</note> he informed me that immediately
                    upon receipt of my protest the Foreign Office had given instructions that the
                    movement of chrome for British account be materially increased. Although he gave
                    me no specific assurance of a decrease in the movement of chrome for German
                    account I gained the impression that this will follow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
